Description: Small fragment of a seal-impression with two rows of basketry coil impression at the rear and at the side one further rows, showing that this piece was positioned most likely on the lid of a basket. The fine brown Nile clay shows small inclusions of mica. The top part wears one complete and the edge of a second impression of a scarab-like seal. The seal impression at the top shows a small cartouche with Mn-khpr-R' in the middle. To the left of it a small column of hieroglyphs [nTr?] nfr nb [...] and on the right side of the cartouche is a winged cobra with the wings pointed towards the cartouche.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
